---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Advertising — Pixel Noise" description="Advertising and sponsorship opportunities on Pixel Noise.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Advertising</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-page-body" style="padding: 0;">
      <p>Pixel Noise reaches an engaged audience of designers, creative directors, UI/UX practitioners, and design-curious technologists. Our readers are professionals who care deeply about craft, tools, and the direction of the industry.</p>
      <p>We offer a range of advertising and partnership formats to connect your brand with this audience in ways that feel natural and respected — not intrusive.</p>
      <p><strong>Sponsored articles</strong> — long-form content written in the Pixel Noise editorial voice that features your product, tool, or service in a genuine, informative way.</p>
      <p><strong>Banner placements</strong> — contextual ad units placed within article pages and category listings, clearly disclosed as advertising.</p>
      <p><strong>Affiliate partnerships</strong> — product and tool recommendations embedded naturally within relevant editorial content. Pixel Noise only recommends products we believe in.</p>
      <p><strong>Newsletter sponsorships</strong> — direct access to our subscriber base through sponsored segments in the Pixel Noise newsletter.</p>
      <p>To discuss rates, formats, and availability, reach out at <a href="mailto:hello@pixelnoise.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline;">hello@pixelnoise.dev</a>.</p>

      <h2>Support Pixel Noise</h2>
      <p>Not ready for a formal advertising arrangement? You can still support Pixel Noise through our Ko-fi page. Every contribution helps keep the writing going and the site independent.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
